article.description: Jonathan Lee had 21 of his career-high 25 points in the second half as Northeastern overcame a 19-point deficit to defeat North Carolina-Asheville on Saturday.
article.headline: Northeastern overcomes 19-point deficit for win
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- Jonathan Lee had 21 of his career-high 25 points in the second half as Northeastern overcame a 19-point deficit to defeat North Carolina-Asheville on Saturday. Chris Stephenson's basket at the buzzer for the Bulldogs was ruled just inside the 3-point line. Chaisson Allen added 18 of his 24 points after the break for the Huskies (10-18), who snapped a two-game skid. UNC Asheville (13-13) led 44-27 at halftime and 48-29 with 18:04 to go before blowing a double-digit lead for the second straight game. Northeastern trailed 77-73 with 2:15 left, then used an 8-1 run to lead 81-78 with 22 seconds to go. After J.P. Primm cut the deficit to one with two free throws, Joel Smith hit a pair for the Huskies for 83-80. Primm missed a 3-pointer with 3 seconds left and Stephenson rebounded to set up his final shot. Matt Dickey scored 23 to lead the Bulldogs.
